	<p>Since you now know the Korean alphabet, you’d think that we would move right along and teach you some Korean words and grammar.</p>

  <p>Good idea, but we’re super lazy teachers, so first we want you to go teach yourself a Korean word. Then maybe (if we can get motivated) We’ll teach you a super useful and easy phrase to learn with your new word.</p>

  <p>The Korean word you are going to teach yourself is………. your name!</p>

  <p>Try to figure out how your name would sound with your new knowledge of Korean sounds and Korean letters.</p>

  <p>Write down your new Korean name and start practicing saying it like a Korean would.</p>

  <p>Okay, got it?</p>

  <p>Now you are going to take your name and and a Korean phrase you will use a lot: “Hi, I am _______.”</p>

  <p>You probably already know hi/hello.</p>

